  "response": "Here are some guidelines for creating Texas driver license exam questions:\n\n1. Content Focus\n- Traffic laws and regulations\n- Road signs and signals\n- Safe driving practices\n- Texas-specific traffic rules\n- Defensive driving techniques\n\n2. Question Types\n- Multiple choice\n- True/false\n- Scenario-based questions\n- Identification of road signs\n\n3. Key Topics to Cover\n- Speed limits\n- Right-of-way rules\n- Parking regulations\n- Alcohol/drug driving laws\n- Seat belt requirements\n- Vehicle equipment standards\n- Intersection navigation\n- Highway driving rules\n\n4. Technical Considerations\n- Clear, concise language\n- Avoid tricky or misleading wording\n- Ensure factual accuracy\n- Align with current Texas Transportation Code\n- Include difficulty variations\n\n5. Exam Structure\n- Comprehensive knowledge test\n- Vision screening\n- Potential skills/road test\n- Different versions for different license types\n\n6. Recommended Resources\n- Texas Department of Public Safety guidelines\n- Current driver's handbook\n- Traffic safety research\n- State legal references\n\nRemember to periodically update exam content to reflect current laws and safety standards.",
